---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import HelpCallout from "../../components/HelpCallout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Older Adults"
  description="Concerned about an older adult's gambling? How to spot the signs and bring it up with care — for adult children, family, and friends."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">
        <a href="/family-and-friends">← Family &amp; friends</a>
      </p>
      <h1>Older Adults</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        Concerned about an older adult's gambling? Here's how to spot the signs
        and bring it up with care — without taking over.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="fnf-top">
    <div class="container fnf-top__grid">
      <div class="fnf-top__main">
        <p>
          Older adults can be especially vulnerable to gambling harm. Fixed
          incomes shrink the margin for losses. Loneliness, recent loss, or
          early cognitive decline can make a casino floor or an online game
          feel like the easiest place to spend an afternoon. And the stigma is
          often sharper at this age — many older adults will never tell their
          adult children that something is wrong.
        </p>
        <p>
          You don't need to be a clinician to help. The most powerful thing you
          can do is open a steady, respectful conversation — and keep it going
          without taking over.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="fnf-top__aside">
        <figure class="fnf-photo">
          <img
            src="/photos/family-and-friends/older-adults.jpg"
            alt="An older parent and adult child sit together in conversation in a cozy home setting."
            width="800"
            height="600"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </figure>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p>
        More detailed guidance — signs to watch for, how to start the
        conversation, what not to do, and how to take care of yourself — is
        being developed for this page. The same framework as the
        <a href="/family-and-friends/youth">Youth</a> page applies; the
        cohort-specific adaptation is in progress.
      </p>
      <HelpCallout />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
